RABIES STATISTICS - USA (TEXAS): JUNE 1999
******************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
See Also
Rabies statistics - USA (Texas): April 1999 990611225106
Rabies statistics - USA (Texas): April 1999 (02) 990620222233
Rabies statistics - USA (Texas): May 1999 990715213707
Date: 20 Aug 1999
From: *Pam Wilson* <Pam.Wilson@tdh.state.tx.us>

During June 1999, there were no cases of canine rabies in South
Texas. To date, no cases of canine rabies have been reported
north of the South Texas Oral Rabies Vaccination Program
(ORVP) drop-zone for coyotes.
In West-Central Texas, there were 3 cases of gray fox rabies in
the following counties: Tom Green (1 bobcat, 1 cat) and Val Verde
(1 fox).
To date, no cases of gray fox rabies have been reported beyond
the boundaries of the original ORVP drop-zone for gray foxes.
There were 20 cases of rabies in animals reported statewide,
including: 11 skunks, 4 bats, 2 cats, 1 fox, 1 bobcat, 1 horse.
Laboratories in Texas that conducted rabies testing on submitted
specimens include: Texas Department of Health, Bureau of
Laboratories, Austin; El Paso City-County Health Department
Laboratory; City of Houston Health Department, Bureau of
Laboratory Services; and San Antonio Metropolitan Health District
Laboratory.
--
Pam Wilson, RVT, MEd, CHES
Texas Department of Health, Zoonosis Control Division
Pam.Wilson@tdh.state.tx.us
[The drop-zones are where oral rabies vaccine has been
distributed. The absence of cases outside those zones suggests
that the campaign to block wildlife rabies is working - Mods.TG &
JW
